The paper focuses on collaborative knowledge building settings, which is a key area of research in computer-supported cooperative work (CSCW). The paper also discusses the use of Wikipedia as a case study, which falls under the category of information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). The proposed method for observing triggering can also be applied to other collaborative settings, such as social media platforms, which fall under the category of social informatics (SI). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (CL) and deep learning (DL).
